    /** New implementation
     * Here, I am updating the method input parameter from CustomerDto to CustomerUpdatedEvent object.
     * First, we need to check if the DB has a customer available for the mobile number that is being updated. If available/If the Customer is existed, I am going to catch it in the Customer reference on the LHS. Otherwise, we are going to throw this ResourceNotFoundException. Here, the resource is 'Customer', and the criteria that we have used to search the customer is 'mobileNumber' and the value that we have used is the mobile number that is being updated as can be visualized in the signature of this ResourceNotFoundException class.
     * After fetching the details from the DB, you need to populate the latest data into this Customer object so that we can eventually send the Customer object to this save method. Earlier on we were using some mapping logic to map the CustomerDto to the Customer object. Now, we are going to use the CustomerMapper class to map the CustomerUpdatedEvent object to the Customer object - check the new method we are creating there which is mapEventToCustomer for more details.
     * Finally, we need to call the save method to save the modified data into the DB.
     *
     * */

    @Override
    public boolean updateCustomer(CustomerUpdatedEvent customerUpdatedEvent) {
        Customer customer = customerRepository.findByMobileNumberAndActiveSw(customerUpdatedEvent.getMobileNumber(), true)
                .orElseThrow(() -> new ResourceNotFoundException("Customer", "mobileNumber", customerUpdatedEvent.getMobileNumber()));
        CustomerMapper.mapEventToCustomer(customerUpdatedEvent, customer);
        customerRepository.save(customer);
        return true;
    }

    /** We already have enough logic related to the Customer Deletion, so we will use the same - no DML here.
     * First we are trying to fetch the customer from the DB using the given customerId. If available, we are going to set the activeSw to IN_ACTIVE_SW and save it into the DB.
     * */
    @Override
    public boolean deleteCustomer(String customerId) {
        Customer customer = customerRepository.findById(customerId).orElseThrow(
                () -> new ResourceNotFoundException("Customer", "customerId", customerId)
        );
        customer.setActiveSw(CustomerConstants.IN_ACTIVE_SW);
        customerRepository.save(customer);
        return true;
    }

